(118, 1, '2023-10-30 05:07:19', '2023-10-30 05:07:19', '<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Introduction:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the middle of the 19th century, realism painting became prominent and began to subvert the romanticism and idealism that were then popular. Realist art sought to capture the world unaltered by embellishment or idealized distortions, stemming from the conviction that art ought to represent the truth of ordinary life. This essay examines the salient features, significant practitioners, and long-lasting effects of Realism painting.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-112 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-12.04.08.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1196\" height=\"544\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Definition and Key Characteristics:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Realism art is characterized by its objective depiction of the world, emphasizing precise representation and attention to detail. It seeks to faithfully capture the physical appearance of subjects, whether they are people, landscapes, or objects. Realist artists strive for accuracy, often employing techniques such as careful observation, meticulous brushwork, and a naturalistic color palette. By focusing on ordinary subjects and the mundane aspects of life, Realism challenges the hierarchy of traditional art and redefines what can be considered artistically significant.</span>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Influential Artists:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gustave Courbet: Regarded as the progenitor of Realism, Courbet tackled contemporary social and political themes in his artwork. His painting \"The Stone Breakers\" is a potent illustration of the movement, showing workers in an unvarnished and raw way and bringing attention to the struggles the working class faces.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-113 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-12.05.29.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1194\" height=\"612\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jean-François Millet: The realities of the agrarian society were made more visible by Millet\'s depictions of rural life and peasant work. Inspiring empathy and social consciousness, his famous painting \"The Gleaners\" depicts the dignity and hardship of rural laborers.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-117 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-12.07.10-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1194\" height=\"878\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Winslow Homer: Homer was an American Realist painter who specialized in depicting scenes from everyday life, especially those of rural communities and fishermen. His paintings, like \"The Gulf Stream\" and \"Snap the Whip,\" capture the wonders and struggles of rural America and life at sea.</span>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li><strong> Impact and Legacy:</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Realism art had a profound influence on the art world and subsequent movements. Its emphasis on truth and authenticity paved the way for later artistic developments, including Impressionism and other modern art movements. Realism challenged the established notions of art, pushing artists to explore new ways of capturing reality and expressing their personal visions. Moreover, Realism played a crucial role in social and political contexts, highlighting societal issues, advocating for change, and giving a voice to marginalized communities.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Conclusion:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Realism art emerged as a powerful response to the prevailing romantic and idealistic art of the 19th century. By depicting the world as it truly is, Realism brought attention to the ordinary, the overlooked, and the marginalized. Its influence continues to resonate in the art world, inspiring artists to explore new ways of capturing reality and challenging societal norms. Realism art serves as a reminder that the beauty and significance of everyday life can be found in the most unassuming places.</span>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Realism Art: Capturing Life\'s Essence', 'A generous donation by artist Lorraine Jenyns and her family of 25 prints, drawings and sculptures by her late husband, the artist Bob Jenyns, adds significantly to an existing collection of his works acquired by the Gallery in the 1980s. Former Gallery Director Margaret Rich recalls her friendship with Bob Jenyns.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '62-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-30 05:07:19', '2023-10-30 05:07:19', '', 62, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=118', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(119, 1, '2023-10-30 05:12:05', '2023-10-30 05:12:05', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Introduction:</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Romanticism as an artistic movement began to take shape in the late 1700s and flourished into the 1800s. It was an emphasis on emotion, imagination, and individualism as a response to the Enlightenment era\'s rationality and order. This article examines the salient features, significant creators, and enduring influence of Romanticism in art.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Body:</span>\n<ol>\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> Definition and Key Characteristics:</strong>\n</span>Romantic art is distinguished by its emphasis on feeling, creativity, and the breathtaking force of nature. It frequently portrayed dramatic and sublime scenes in an effort to elicit strong emotional reactions from viewers. Romantic artists investigated themes of passion, individualism, and the paranormal, embracing the subjective experience. Their unconventional compositions, spontaneity, and self-expression were valued over the strict guidelines of academic art.</li>\n</ol>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> Influential Artists:</strong>\n</span>Caspar David Friedrich: Friedrich\'s lone figures and eerie landscapes embodied the Romantic spirit in his works. The figure in his painting \"Wanderer above the Sea of Fog\" looks out into a vast and enigmatic landscape, perfectly capturing the sense of wonder and introspection associated with Romanticism.</li>\n</ol>\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-120 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-12.10.21.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1190\" height=\"576\" />\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">J.M.W. Turner: Turner\'s paintings, which frequently had a dramatic and atmospheric flair, emphasized the strength and beauty of nature. As demonstrated in pieces like \"The Fighting Temeraire\" and \"Rain, Steam, and Speed,\" his use of color and light inspires wonder and portrays the sublime in the natural world.</span>\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-121 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/trasua/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Screenshot-2023-10-30-at-12.12.24.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1194\" height=\"668\" />\n\n&nbsp;', 'Romanticism Art: The Romantic Spirit in Visual Form', 'A generous donation by artist Lorraine Jenyns and her family of 25 prints, drawings and sculptures by her late husband, the artist Bob Jenyns, adds significantly to an existing collection of his works acquired by the Gallery in the 1980s. Former Gallery Director Margaret Rich recalls her friendship with Bob Jenyns.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '61-autosave-v1', '', '', '2023-10-30 05:12:05', '2023-10-30 05:12:05', '', 61, 'http://localhost/trasua/?p=119', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
